    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 2C: Lasp1 expression was enriched in PSD fractions, PSD-95 was used as a positive control.\nFigure 5A-D: Punctate pattern of Lasp1 immunolabelling overlays with postsynaptic marker, PSD-95.\nFigure 5E: To ensure its localisation on the postsynapse, Lasp1-GFP was transfected into hippocampal neurons and the expression was seen on dendritic spines.\nFigure 6: Preembedding immunoelectron microscopy demonstrate prominent labelling at the postsynaptic compartment.\n\nNote on the antibody used: the paper does not comment on antibody specificity.\n\nTaken together, the SynGO term 'postsynapse' was used.. Experimental description: Hippocampal neuronal cultures were derived from Spague-Dawley rats (18 days of gestation).",
